Sentencas: Iron-stabilized lanthanum nickelate oxide with a perovskite structure, LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3-delta(LNF), was prepared by a citrate-nitrate process and evaluated as the cathode component of a proton-conducting SOFC based on a Ba(Zr0.1Ce0.7Y0.2)O-3-delta (BZCY) electrolyte.
Titulo: High-performance anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells based on nickel-based cathode and Ba(Zr0.1Ce0.7Y0.2)O3-δ electrolyte

Sentencas: XRD analysis shows that LNF reacts with BZCY to form a K2NiF4-type phase in the course of cathode calcination, but remains chemically well compatible with BZCY at the operating temperature.
Titulo: High-performance anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells based on nickel-based cathode and Ba(Zr0.1Ce0.7Y0.2)O3-δ electrolyte

Sentencas: A single cell was assembled and tested using humidified hydrogen as fuel gas and atmospheric air as the oxidant.
Titulo: High-performance anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells based on nickel-based cathode and Ba(Zr0.1Ce0.7Y0.2)O3-δ electrolyte

Sentencas: The matching thermal expansion coefficient (TEC), high conductivity and good catalytic activity of the LNF cathode enable the cell to generate high power densities and low polarization resistances.
Titulo: High-performance anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells based on nickel-based cathode and Ba(Zr0.1Ce0.7Y0.2)O3-δ electrolyte

Sentencas: At 700 degrees C, the peak power density is 668mWcm(-2) and the polarization resistance is 0.046 Omega cm(2).
Titulo: High-performance anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells based on nickel-based cathode and Ba(Zr0.1Ce0.7Y0.2)O3-δ electrolyte

Sentencas: This work confirms that LNF may be a prospective cathode material for BZCY proton-conducting electrolytes.(C) 2013
Titulo: High-performance anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells based on nickel-based cathode and Ba(Zr0.1Ce0.7Y0.2)O3-δ electrolyte
